style="width:32.233%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:32.233%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:32.234%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr style="height:15pt"><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table></div><div style="text-align:right"><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:0.08pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:125%">smoke-free products for adults who would otherwise continue to smoke, with the goal of completely ending the sale of cigarettes. This includes the building of world-class scientific assessment capabilities, notably in the areas of pre-clinical systems toxicology, clinical and behavioral research, as well as post-market studies. The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has authorized the marketing of versions of PMI's </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:125%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:125%"> Platform 1 devices and consumables as modified risk tobacco products (MRTPs), finding that exposure modification orders for these products are appropriate to promote the public health. As of March 31, 2022, PMI's smoke-free products were available for sale in 71 markets, and PMI estimates that approximately 12.7 million adults around the world, excluding Russia and Ukraine, had already switched to </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:125%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:125%"> and stopped smoking. With a strong foundation and significant expertise in life sciences, in February 2021 PMI announced its ambition to expand into wellness and healthcare areas and deliver innovative products and solutions that aim to address unmet consumer and patient needs.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:0.08pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:8pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">PMI is an American corporation, incorporated in Virginia and headquartered in New York City, in the United States of America. PMI's shares are traded on the New York Stock Exchange.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:0.08pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:8pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">For more information, please visit www.pmi.com and www.pmiscience.com.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6.75pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Financing of the Offer</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The consideration payable in respect of the Offer is fully secured by funds which PMI has undertaken to contribute, directly or indirectly, to PMHH. PMI's undertaking to contribute funds is fully secured by funds available to PMI pursuant to debt financing committed to be provided by Bank of America and Citi on terms which are customary for the financing of public offers.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The above-mentioned undertaking from PMI and financing will provide PMHH with sufficient cash resources to satisfy in full the consideration payable in respect of the Offer and, accordingly, completion of the Offer is not subject to any financing condition.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6.75pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Review of information in connection with the Offer</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">PMHH has been permitted by the board of directors of Swedish Match to carry out a limited confirmatory due diligence review of Swedish Match in connection with the preparation of the Offer. Except for the interim report for January &#8211; March 2022, which will be made public by Swedish Match on May 11, 2022, Swedish Match has informed PMHH that no inside information has been disclosed to PMHH during the process.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6.75pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Approvals from authorities</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The completion of the Offer is conditional upon, </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">inter alia</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">, all necessary regulatory, governmental or similar clearances, approvals, decisions and other actions from authorities or similar, including from competition authorities being obtained, in each case on terms which, in PMHH's opinion, are acceptable. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">According to PMHH's assessment, the transaction will require customary merger control approvals (and foreign direct investment approvals) including in the European Union, the United States, and Brazil. PMHH has initiated the work on filings relevant for the transaction. PMHH expects relevant clearances to be obtained prior to the end of the acceptance period.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6.75pt"><font ruling AMN 2022&#58;20 granted an exemption from Rule II.7 of the Takeover Rules for Nasdaq Stockholm (the &#34;</font><font publication of the offer document. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;text-align:justify"><font PMHH has, in accordance with the Swedish Act on Public Takeovers on the Stock Market (Sw.&#160;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">lagen (2006&#58;451) om offentliga uppk&#246;pserbjudanden p&#229; aktiemarknaden</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">), on May 10, 2022, undertaken to Nasdaq Stockholm AB (&#34;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Nasdaq</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">&#34;) to fully comply with such rules and statements and to be subject to any sanctions that may be imposed by Nasdaq in event of a breach of the Takeover Rules. On&#160;May&#160;11,&#160;2022, PMHH informed the Swedish Financial Supervisory Authority (Sw.&#160;</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Finansinspektionen</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">) about the Offer and the above-mentioned undertaking towards Nasdaq.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6.75pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Advisors</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:125%">BofA Securities and Citigroup Global Markets Limited are acting as financial advisors to PMHH in connection with the Offer. var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
